<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,293,618]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,264,330,356]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<typeStatus box="[196,256,330,356]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In Faust’s collection at 
<collectionCode box="[561,648,330,356]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">SMTD</collectionCode>
, is a male (right elytron pinned, left funicle missing) bearing the handwritten labels: “[golden square]”, “ 
<number box="[630,652,367,393]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
, Albasin, Must.”, and fitting the description with 
<typeStatus box="[1254,1305,368,394]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
locality as Albasin. It is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[536,643,405,431]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">lectotype</typeStatus>
with “ 
<typeStatus box="[721,857,405,431]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lectotypus</typeStatus>
, 
<number box="[870,892,404,430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Faust, Gultekin" authorityName="Faust, Gultekin" box="[908,1264,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="posticus">
<emphasis box="[908,1075,405,430]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lixus posticus</emphasis>
Faust, Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number box="[1327,1391,405,431]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2005.0">2005</number>
”. A male and a female (right elytron pinned, left fore leg and right middle claw segment of male missing, elytra of female separated) bear the labels: “[golden square]”, “ 
<number box="[822,844,479,505]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
, Chabarofka Basin”, and are here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[151,320,517,543]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
with “ 
<typeStatus box="[397,575,517,543]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Paralectotypus</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Faust, Gultekin" authorityName="Faust, Gultekin" box="[587,941,517,543]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="posticus">
<emphasis box="[587,754,517,542]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lixus posticus</emphasis>
Faust, Gültekin
</taxonomicName>
des. 
<number box="[1002,1066,517,543]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2005.0">2005</number>
”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,293,618]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,318,554,580]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hochhuth" authorityName="Hochhuth" box="[627,954,554,580]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nordmanni">
<emphasis box="[627,827,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Lixus nordmanni</emphasis>
Hochhuth
</taxonomicName>
, but clearly differs by its thick and short rostrum, and sharp apex of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
